Add an RSS feed for works, to be used by discovery for indexing

comments.body: I'm curious: why use RSS here instead of OAI-PMH?

@escowles My thought was that RSS is easy to implement and the main thing I'm trying to accomplish here is a list of content to index for discovery. We know we eventually want an OAI-PMH feed on Discovery (or do we? I've also heard we want ResourceSync instead?) I thought I'd be opening a can of worms by implementing OAI and that it would be scope creep past what I need to deliver for the ticket I'm working on. Glad to revisit this decision if you have more information than I do or would prefer a different approach.
@bess Those are all good reasons to use RSS — I was mostly just surprised.

comments.body:
- `processinfo` is searchable and appears in hit highlighting.
- In this ticket, ensure that `acqinfo_teim` is indexed.

@phoebeno @faithc This is easy to do for collection records, but I'm unclear about what to do on components. Is the suggestion that components should index `acqinfo` and `processinfo` values inherited from their parents? Right now, if a component has a `processinfo` value, that value is indexed as is searchable. [Example query](https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog?q=%22This+description+was+updated+by+Kelly+Bolding+in+2021+based+on+information+provided+by+a+researcher+to+indicate+that+the+people+pictured+are+likely+a+Kiowa+family%2C+not+a+Cheyenne+family%2C+as+was+previously+indicated.%22&search_field=all_fields). There are 214 components with their own `processinfo` field.

After PR #1144 is merged, the same will be true of `acqinfo`.
